[{"id":"VR618525","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A small block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase m\"><math alttext=\"lowercase m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> is moving along a horizontal surface when it collides with a large block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"uppercase M\"><math alttext=\"uppercase M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>M</mi></math></span></span>, which is initially at rest. Friction between the blocks and surface is negligible and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase m is less than uppercase M\"><math alttext=\"lowercase m is less than uppercase M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>M</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following statements correctly compares the magnitude of the acceleration <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub S\"><math alttext=\"a sub S\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>S</mtext></msub></math></span></span> of the small block to the magnitude of the acceleration <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub L\"><math alttext=\"a sub L\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>L</mtext></msub></math></span></span> of the large block during the collision and provides a correct justification?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR618525_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub S is greater than a sub L\"><math alttext=\"a sub S is greater than a sub L\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>S</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>L</mtext></msub></math></span></span> because the large block exerts a greater force on the small block than the small block exerts on the large block.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub S is greater than a sub L\"><math alttext=\"a sub S is greater than a sub L\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>S</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>L</mtext></msub></math></span></span> because the small block has less mass than the large block and the blocks exert forces of equal magnitude on each other.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub S equals a sub L\"><math alttext=\"a sub S equals a sub L\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>S</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>L</mtext></msub></math></span></span> because Newtonâ€™s third law states that every action has an equal and opposite reaction.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub S equals a sub L\"><math alttext=\"a sub S equals a sub L\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>S</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>L</mtext></msub></math></span></span> because the acceleration of the center of mass of the two-block system is zero as there is no external net force exerted on the system.</p>"],"answer":1}]